---
import { Link } from "@avaya/neo-react";

import {
	CollapsibleColumns,
	Description,
	ExternalLink,
	ImageWithCaption,
	InfoList,
	InfoListItem,
	PageleteSection,
	PageleteSubSection,
	SectionHeader,
	SubHeader,
} from "components";

import image4 from "../imgs/interactions-1.svg";
import image5 from "../imgs/interactions-3.svg";
import image6 from "../imgs/interactions-4.svg";
import image3 from "../imgs/interactions-5.svg";
import image1 from "../imgs/user-interface-1.svg";
import image2 from "../imgs/user-interface-2.svg";

import { topics } from "../static";
const { id, title } = topics.mac;
---

<PageleteSection>
  <SectionHeader id={id}>{title}</SectionHeader>

  <Description>
    MacOS is a desktop operating system created by Apple that is used on their
    computer systems. An overview of Apple's best practices can be found in
    their <ExternalLink
      href="https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines"
      inline
    >
      Human Interface Guidelines
    </ExternalLink>.
  </Description>

  <PageleteSubSection>
    <SubHeader id="mac-user-interface">User Interface</SubHeader>

    <Description>
      The visual appearance for MacOS applications should utilize a combination
      of native elements and Neo styling.
    </Description>

    <CollapsibleColumns>
      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image1.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing various elements."
        captionTitle="Native Elements"
      >
        Applications built for MacOS should use native components wherever
        possible to ensure consistency across platforms, while leveraging
        built-in accessibility. Neo should be applied at the design token level
        by leveraging our colors, font and icons where possible.
      </ImageWithCaption>

      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image2.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing icons."
        captionTitle="Icons"
      >
        All non-system icons used by MacOS applications are available on the
        icons page.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/icons">View Icon Library</Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>
    </CollapsibleColumns>
  </PageleteSubSection>

  <PageleteSubSection>
    <SubHeader id="mac-interactions">Interactions</SubHeader>

    <Description>
      Interactions such as display, responsiveness, accessibility and touch
      targets should follow web standards, as well as the Neo guidelines found
      throughout the portal.
    </Description>

    <CollapsibleColumns>
      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image3.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing keyboard keys."
        captionTitle="Keyboard Shortcuts"
      >
        Shortcuts created for MacOS applications must not conflict with existing
        OS or screen reader shortcuts. Refer to the <ExternalLink
          href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201236"
          inline
        >
          Apple keyboard shortcuts
        </ExternalLink>
        and <ExternalLink
          href="https://support.apple.com/guide/voiceover/welcome/mac"
          inline
        >
          Voiceover documentation
        </ExternalLink> for the complete list.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/accessibility/keyboard-interactions">
              View Keyboard interactions
            </Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>

      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image4.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing responsive display sizes."
        captionTitle="Display and Responsive Size"
      >
        Layouts need to be flexible and responsive, with scaling to match
        different screen sizes. Accurate proportions improve the composition and
        hierarchy. This ensures consistency and a common user experience across
        all platforms.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/guidelines/layout-grid">View Layout and Grid</Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>
    </CollapsibleColumns>

    <CollapsibleColumns>
      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image5.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing accessibility."
        captionTitle="Accessibility"
      >
        MacOS applications must be accessible to all users. Learn more with <ExternalLink
          href="https://support.apple.com/guide/mac-help/get-started-with-accessibility-features-mh35884/mac"
          inline
        >
          Apple's documentation
        </ExternalLink> and our accessibility guidelines.

        <InfoList>
          <InfoListItem>
            <Link href="/guidelines/accessibility">View Accessibility</Link>
          </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>
      </ImageWithCaption>

      <ImageWithCaption
        imgSrc={image6.src}
        imgAlt="Graphic representing touch targets."
        captionTitle="Touch Targets"
      >
        Interactive controls, such as buttons, should have a minimum 44pt x 44pt
        tappable area making them easy to see and use, and to meet
        <ExternalLink
          href="https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/accessibility"
          inline
        >
          Apple's specifications
        </ExternalLink>.
      </ImageWithCaption>
    </CollapsibleColumns>
  </PageleteSubSection>
</PageleteSection>
